comment: Teague (IND) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Hill (UTA) that affects his shot attempt.
Turner (IND) firms up his position and sets the screen on Hayward (UTA).
Hill (UTA) makes incidental contact with George (IND) that does not affect his SQBR.
Hayward (UTA) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with George (IND) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Turner (IND) makes incidental contact with Gobert (UTA) during rebounding.
Ingles (UTA) makes incidental contact with George (IND) that does not affect his SQBR.
Turner (IND) moves into Ingles' (UTA) path and delivers the contact on the screen.
Gobert (UTA) obtains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Ellis (IND) on his driving shot attempt.
George (IND) makes incidental contact with Ingles (UTA) during the loose ball.
[Detectable with stop watch] Turner (IND) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Teague (IND) makes incidental contact with Hayward (UTA) that does not affect his FOM.
George (IND) makes contact with the ball and the part of Gobert's (UTA) hand that is considered part of the ball.
Gobert (UTA) sets the screen on Young (IND) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Gobert (UTA) pushes Turner (IND) and dislodges him from his rebounding position.
Turner (IND) legally contests Hill's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
Young (IND) and Hill (UTA) make incidental contact with one another during the loose ball.
Johnson (UTA) commits a take foul on Teague (IND).
Neto (UTA) commits a take foul on George (IND).
